Date: 0/0/1874
Source: Colonial Experiences
Author: BATHGATE
Vol / Page: 97
Edition:
Quote: <i>Miners' Expressions:</i> ... There are many words and phrases current peculiar to the mining population ... Besides [technical expressions] there are words used in general conversation which would not be found in an English dictionary. Such, for example, as `duffer' or `shiser', anything that is useless.
